<section class="instructions">
  <h1>Configure Git</h1>
  <ol>
    <li>
      In your Ubuntu terminal type:
      <pre><code>git config --global user.name "<strong>Your Actual Name</strong>"</code></pre>
    </li>

    <li>
      And then type:
      <pre><code>git config --global user.email "<strong>Your Actual Email</strong>"</code></pre>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12 note" id="prompt" style="text-align:center;">
          Your email address should be the same one associated with your <%= link_to "GitHub", "http://help.github.com/articles/set-up-git", target: "_blank" %> account. If you don't have a GitHub account already, <%= link_to 'sign up', 'https://github.com' %> for free.
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li>
      Generate an SSH key for your GitHub account:
      <pre><code>ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "YOUR@EMAIL.com"</code></pre>
      Now display it inside your terminal:
      <pre><code>cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub</code></pre>
      And next you should <%= link_to 'copy/paste the output here', 'https://github.com/settings/ssh/new', target: :_blank %>
      as a new SSH key (requires GitHub login).
      <div class="text-center"><%= image_tag "windows/github-add-ssh-key.png", class: "img img-responsive" %></div>
      (Your SSH key will begin with "ssh-rsa ...." and end with details about your computer.)
    </li>

    <li>
      Check your configuration via:
      <pre><code>ssh -T git@github.com</code></pre>
    </li>

    <li>
      You should see a message like:
      <pre><code>Hi username! You've successfully...</code></pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <hr>

  <div class="center" id="git-intro">
    <h2>Why did we do this? What is Git?</h2>
    <p>
    Git is version control software. You will use Git to track and manage your coding history as well as get into the programming community as a whole.
    </p>
    <p>
    Later in the <%= link_to 'Fundamentals course', ENV['FUNDAMENTALS_COURSE_URL'], target: :_blank %> we'll provide a tutorial to get started with Git. For now, just install and forget about it.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

